To answer your question, the most important physical law governing the quantity of energy in a system is the law of conservation of energy.

This fundamental principle states that energy cannot be created or destroyed, only transformed from one form to another.  In a closed system, the total amount of energy remains constant, even though it may change forms ‚Äì from potential to kinetic, from chemical to thermal, and so on. ¬† 

